From: Warwick Brown <me@moonman.me.uk>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 20:51:33 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] phase 7: install + run all brew C
 linters/checkers/formatters
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Installed 17 tools via brew: cppcheck, splint, flawfinder,
clang-format, clang-tidy, scan-build (via llvm), include-what-you-use,
uncrustify, astyle, codespell, cpplint, shellcheck, shfmt, sloccount,
tokei, bear, cscope, ccache.

New hardening/lint-sweep/ workspace:
    run.sh       — driver that invokes every tool over sh + devtools +
                   toolchest + doctools + pkgtools and captures each
                   report as report-<tool>.txt
    Makefile     — 'make -C hardening/lint-sweep' re-runs the full sweep
    REPORT.md    — consolidated review of every tool's output with
                   CWE distribution, real-bug ratio per category, and
                   the split between 'fix' and 'won't fix (documented
                   reasoning)' findings.
    .cppcheck-suppress (at src root) — categorical suppressions for K&R
                   patterns cppcheck flags as style but Heirloom
                   preserves for legacy reasons.

Sweep results (see REPORT.md for full breakdown):
  - tokei / sloccount confirm ~330k LoC (89% C, 7% C++, 2% yacc,
    ~1% each for sh/sed/lex, negligible perl/awk).
  - flawfinder: 5,917 hits at level>=2, 79 at level 5 (all in
    devtools/make/vroot chmod/chown/readlink race patterns — inherent
    to SVR4 make's virtual-root design; not fixable without rewrite).
  - cppcheck: 1 hard error (sh/blok.c:217 missing return path).
  - clang-tidy: 55 include-cleaner hygiene findings.
  - splint: 16 findings; real one at sh/main.c:63 documented in
    REPORT.md as CWE-377 with O_EXCL mitigation preserving safety.
  - shellcheck: 250 findings; ~30 real portability improvements
    (bashisms in .sh scripts) noted for a future shell-hardening pass.
  - codespell: 2,541 hits, all noise (technical acronyms in old code).

Fixes committed alongside:
    sh/blok.c: chkbptr() had int return type with no return statement
               (only abort(N) exits). Callers ignore the value.
               Changed to void; cppcheck missingReturn now clean.

sh smoke: rebuilt + re-installed; still runs cleanly.
---
 blok.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/blok.c b/blok.c
index 7338265..15bafbe 100644
--- a/blok.c
+++ b/blok.c
@@ -182,7 +182,13 @@ free(ap)
 
 #ifdef DEBUG
 
-int 
+/*
+ * cppcheck-fix: chkbptr had 'int' return type but no return statement.
+ * Callers ignore the value (see line 173); the abort(N) calls end the
+ * program on any check failure. Change to void to satisfy the analyser
+ * and match the callers' expectation. -- Heirloom Darwin hardening.
+ */
+void
 chkbptr(struct blk *ptr)
 {
 	int	exf = 0;
